Most Used HTTP Status Codes (API-friendly)
Code	Name	Meaning / Use Case
200 OK	Success	Request succeeded (GET, PUT, DELETE). Returns data.
201 Created	Created	New resource created (POST). Returns new resource ID.
204 No Content	No Content	Request succeeded, but no data returned (DELETE or PUT).
400 Bad Request	Client error	Invalid request, missing required fields, validation errors.
401 Unauthorized	Authentication error	User not logged in or token invalid.
403 Forbidden	Forbidden	User logged in but not allowed to perform action.
404 Not Found	Not Found	Resource (ID) doesnâ€™t exist.
409 Conflict	Conflict	Duplicate record or conflicting request.
422 Unprocessable Entity	Validation error	Semantic errors (e.g., invalid email format).
429 Too Many Requests	Rate limiting	Too many requests in a short period.
500 Internal Server Error	Server error	Generic server-side failure.
502 Bad Gateway	Server error	Upstream server error (if using proxy).
503 Service Unavailable	Server error	Server temporarily unavailable or maintenance.
504 Gateway Timeout	Server error	Upstream server timed out.